The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Nation at a Glance

 Security stepped up for stars

 Mumbai (PTI): Security for Sachin Tendulkar, 

 Amitabh Bachchan, Shah Rukh Khan and other prominent residents 

 of Mumbai has been stepped up following intelligence reports 

 that they could be terror targets, police said on Saturday.

 Tendulkar, who enjoys Y-category security, will be accompanied by armed bodyguards whereever he goes, while his Mumbai residence and other places he visits in the country will be guarded by local policemen.

 The police, however, refused to reveal the nature of security to be provided to other icons like Bachchan, Shah Rukh and industrialist Mukesh Ambani.

 Govt forms five film panels

 New Delhi: The information and broadcasting 

 ministry has decided to set up five core groups to look 

 into the export of films, piracy, exhibition, development 

 of archives, concerns over taxes and customs, and film festivals 

 in India and abroad, reports our special correspondent.

 I amp;B minister Priya Ranjan Das Munshi announced the decision at a meeting with representatives from the film industry on Saturday.

 Filmmaker Shyam Benegal and actors Shatrughan Sinha, Dharmendra and Sharmila Tagore (in PTI picture above) were among those who attended the meeting.

 The core groups will comprise representatives from the film industry, I amp;B ministry officials and business chambers like Ficci.

 Calcutta fire

 Calcutta:Fire engulfed offices on the 

 third floor of 4 Poddar Court in the heart of Calcuttas 

 business district on Saturday evening.

 The floor houses offices of the income-tax department. The blaze, ignited by a gas cylinder explosion, was controlled by 25 fire engines in an hour

 Bharti address

 New Delhi (PTI): The England address 

 purportedly given by Bharti Yadav, prime witness in the 

 Nitish Katara murder case, has been confirmed by the external 

 affairs ministry, the prosecution told a court here on Saturday. 

 The basis for the confirmation was not mentioned in the 

 ministrys report, the prosecution said.

 Bomb explosion

 Puri (PTI): A bomb exploded near the 

 mutt of the Puri Shankaracharya, Swami Nischalananda Saraswati, 

 on Saturday. Police retrieved another unexploded bomb later. 

 The Orissa State Commission for Women has joined the battle against high mortality during childbirth with the launch of safe motherhood adalats in 15 districts across the state.




